back cameras at the same time, and Pause &amp; Resume recording that brings Vine-style seamless video cuts. Check out the video to experience it for yourself, we'll see if LG's phablet can beat the Galaxy S4 -- and, presumably, the next Galaxy Note -- to market in the US with these features.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/cellphones/" rel="tag">Cellphones</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/mobile/" rel="tag">Mobile</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/lg/" rel="tag">LG</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/10/lg-optimus-g-pro-value-pack-video-preview/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BrJ9HKhfSgU">LGMobileHQ (YouTube)</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"a80a02666183e4237b17ed44c0f223e2";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:53:"Impulsive Furnishing Unit wins Frame Moooi Award 2013";s:4:"link";s:53:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/dezeen/~3/3EINwWQoYrY/";s:6:"author";s:16:"Emilie Chalcraft";s:4:"date";i:1365623774;s:7:"content";s:1631:"<p><a href="http://www.dezeen.com/?p=307387"><img title="Impulsive Furnishing Unit" src="http://static.dezeen.com/uploads/2013/04/dezeen_Impulsive-Furnishing-Unit_1sqa.jpg" alt="Impulsive Furnishing Unit" width="468" height="468"></a></p>
